var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"guide/cross-library/#Cross-Library-Features","page":"Cross-Library Features","text":"Wicked borrows proven ideas from the wider TUI ecosystem and makes them idiomatic Julia. These helpers currently live on the Wicked module (reach them with import Wicked) and are ready to promote into Wicked.API.\n\nusing Wicked.API\nimport Wicked","title":"Cross-Library Features"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/cross-library/#Scoped-styling-DSL-(Terminus-/-Compose-/-Lip-Gloss)","page":"Cross-Library Features","text":"A nestable, scoped styling DSL that builds a native Text. Inner scopes merge onto the enclosing style, and each scope restores the previous style on exit — the Terminus foreground.green { … } feel, with Compose-style nesting.\n\ndoc = Wicked.styled_text() do b\n    Wicked.styled(b; fg=:cyan, bold=true) do\n        Wicked.emit!(b, \"Deploy \")\n        Wicked.styled(b; fg=:green) do\n            Wicked.emit!(b, \"ready\")               # inherits bold, overrides fg\n        end\n    end\n    Wicked.newline!(b)\n    Wicked.emit!(b, \"press q to quit\"; dim=true)   # one-shot styled fragment\nend\n\nrender!(Frame(Buffer(2, 24)), Paragraph(doc), Rect(1, 1, 2, 24))\n\nKeywords: fg, bg, underline_color, bold, dim, italic, underline, reverse, strikethrough, blink. Colors may be Color values, Symbols, or strings (via parse_color).","title":"🪢 Scoped styling DSL (Terminus / Compose / Lip Gloss)"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/cross-library/#Spring-physics-(Harmonica)","page":"Cross-Library Features","text":"A numerically-stable damped-spring integrator for natural motion — smooth scrolling, progress easing, cursor glide.\n\nspring = Wicked.Spring(1/60; angular_frequency=8.0, damping_ratio=0.6)\nposition, velocity = 0.0, 0.0\nfor _ in 1:120\n    position, velocity = Wicked.spring_update(spring, position, velocity, 1.0)\nend\n\ndamping_ratio < 1 overshoots and settles; = 1 is critically damped; > 1 is slow with no overshoot.","title":"🌊 Spring physics (Harmonica)"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/cross-library/#Adaptive-color-and-downsampling-(Lip-Gloss)","page":"Cross-Library Features","text":"# Pick a light/dark variant for the terminal background\nWicked.adaptive_color(\"black\", \"white\"; dark_background=true)   # → AnsiColor(white)\n\n# Reduce a truecolor value to a lower profile, returning a Color\nWicked.downsample_color(RGBColor(255, 128, 0), :ansi256)        # 6×6×6 cube\nWicked.downsample_color(RGBColor(255, 128, 0), :ansi16)         # intensity+dominant\n\nThe downsampling uses the exact quantisation the ANSI backend applies, so a pre-downsampled color renders identically to letting the backend degrade it.","title":"🌗 Adaptive color & downsampling (Lip Gloss)"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/cross-library/#Keybinding-help-(Bubble-Tea-key-help)","page":"Cross-Library Features","text":"A single binding source of truth (key + description + enabled) that drives both the footer and a width-truncated help line.\n\nbinds = [\n    Wicked.KeyBinding(\"q\", \"quit\"),\n    Wicked.KeyBinding(\"s\", \"save\"; enabled=document_dirty),\n    Wicked.KeyBinding(\"?\", \"help\"),\n]\n\nFooter(Wicked.help_hints(binds))                 # feeds Footer / HelpView\nWicked.short_help(binds; max_width=40)           # \"q quit • s save • …\"\n\nhelp_hints returns KeyHints for the enabled bindings; short_help renders a single line, dropping entries with an overflow marker to fit max_width.","title":"⌨️ Keybinding help (Bubble Tea key + help)"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/cross-library/#Multi-resolution-canvas-markers-(Ratatui-markers)","page":"Cross-Library Features","text":"Draw on a sub-cell pixel grid and render it with a choice of glyph markers, trading resolution for terminal compatibility.\n\ncanvas = Wicked.PixelCanvas(4, 8; marker=:quadrant)   # :braille :quadrant :half_block :dot\nWicked.pixel_set!(canvas, 3, 5)\nrows = Wicked.pixel_render(canvas)                     # Vector{String}, one per cell row\n\nMarker Resolution / cell Notes\n:braille 2×4 Highest density (U+2800 block).\n:quadrant 2×2 Universally supported block quadrants.\n:half_block 1×2 Upper/lower half block.\n:dot 1×1 Coarsest, maximal compatibility.","title":"🖼️ Multi-resolution canvas markers (Ratatui markers)"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/cross-library/#Overlapping-layout-(Ratatui-Spacing::Overlap)","page":"Cross-Library Features","text":"Lay out segments that share cells with their neighbours — for blocks that share a border — without touching the flex engine.\n\nWicked.overlap_layout(Rect(1, 1, 3, 20), [10, 10]; overlap=1)   # share 1 column\nWicked.overlap_layout(Rect(1, 1, 3, 20), [10, 10]; overlap=0)   # abut, no overlap","title":"🧩 Overlapping layout (Ratatui Spacing::Overlap)"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/hello-world/#Tutorial:-Hello,-World","page":"Hello, World","text":"The smallest possible Wicked program. It shows the one idea everything else builds on: you render widgets into a Buffer, and a buffer can be inspected as plain text — no terminal required.\n\nThe complete file is examples/hello_world.jl. Run it with:\n\njulia --project=. examples/hello_world.jl","title":"Tutorial: Hello, World"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/hello-world/#The-whole-program","page":"Hello, World","text":"using Wicked.API\n\n# 1. Make a buffer: 3 rows tall, 34 columns wide.\nbuffer = Buffer(3, 34)\n\n# 2. Render a bordered panel containing a paragraph into the whole buffer.\nrender!(\n    Frame(buffer),\n    Panel(Paragraph(\"Hello, Wicked!\"); block=Block(title=\"hello\")),\n    buffer.area,\n)\n\n# 3. Look at the result.\nprintln(plain_snapshot(buffer))","title":"The whole program"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/hello-world/#What-it-prints","page":"Hello, World","text":"╭─hello──────────────────────────╮\n│Hello, Wicked!                  │\n╰────────────────────────────────╯","title":"What it prints"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/hello-world/#Line-by-line","page":"Hello, World","text":"Buffer(3, 34) — a grid of styled cells, 3 rows by 34 columns. This is the render target. In a real app the terminal backend owns one of these; here we make our own so we can print it.\nFrame(buffer) — a per-frame handle over the buffer. render! accepts a Buffer or a Frame.\nParagraph(\"Hello, Wicked!\") — wrappable, styled text.\nPanel(...; block=Block(title=\"hello\")) — a bordered container. Block carries the border and title; Panel renders a child inside it.\nrender!(target, widget, area) — draws the widget into area (here buffer.area, the whole buffer).\nplain_snapshot(buffer) — returns the on-screen text with styling stripped. This is what makes Wicked trivial to test: assert on the text.","title":"Line by line"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/hello-world/#Next","page":"Hello, World","text":"Add explicit state and input in Immediate Mode.\nBuild a real interactive app in the Weather App tutorial.","title":"Next"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/runtime/#Managed-Runtime","page":"Managed Runtime","text":"The managed runtime is Wicked's Elm-style application model. Your app owns a model; update! changes it and returns a command; app_view renders it. The runtime owns the loop, timers, async work, and cleanup — one observable lifecycle.","title":"Managed Runtime"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/runtime/#Define-an-app","page":"Managed Runtime","text":"using Wicked.API\nimport Wicked.API: app_view, initialize, update!\n\nmutable struct CounterModel\n    count::Int\nend\n\nstruct CounterApp <: WickedApp end\n\ninitialize(::CounterApp) = CounterModel(0)\n\napp_view(::CounterApp, m::CounterModel) =\n    Panel(Paragraph(\"count = $(m.count)\"); block=Block(title=\"Counter\"))\n\nfunction update!(::CounterApp, m::CounterModel, msg)\n    msg === :increment && (m.count += 1; return FrameCommand())\n    msg === :tick      && return DelayCommand(0.25, :increment)\n    msg === :quit      && return ExitCommand(m.count)\n    return NoCommand()\nend\n\nYou implement three methods on your app type:\n\ninitialize(app) → the initial model.\napp_view(app, model) → a widget (or Toolkit element) to render.\nupdate!(app, model, message) → mutate the model, return a command.","title":"Define an app"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/runtime/#Commands","page":"Managed Runtime","text":"Commands are the runtime's vocabulary for effects. update! returns one:\n\nCommand Effect\nNoCommand() Do nothing.\nFrameCommand() Request a redraw.\nMessageCommand(msg) Deliver another message now.\nDelayCommand(seconds, msg) Deliver msg after a delay (a timer).\nBatchCommand(cmds...) Run several commands.\nExitCommand(result) Stop the app and return result.\n\nThis mirrors Bubble Tea's Cmd/Batch/Tick and Elm's command model.","title":"Commands"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/runtime/#Drive-it-headlessly","page":"Managed Runtime","text":"You do not need a real terminal to run — or test — an app. A RuntimePilot plus virtual time gives you full control:\n\npilot = RuntimePilot(CounterApp(); height=3, width=24)\n@assert occursin(\"count = 0\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nsend!(pilot, :increment)\n@assert occursin(\"count = 1\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nsend!(pilot, :tick)\nadvance_time!(pilot, 0.25)                 # fast-forward the timer\n@assert occursin(\"count = 2\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nresult = send!(pilot, :quit)\n@assert result.exited\n\nadvance_time! deterministically fires timers and subscriptions — no sleeping, no flakiness. See Testing for more.\n\nThe full runnable version is in examples/runtime_quickstart.jl.","title":"Drive it headlessly"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/testing/#Testing","page":"Testing","text":"Because every widget renders into a Buffer, Wicked apps are fast and deterministic to test — no real terminal required. Wicked ships pilots, snapshots, semantic queries, and virtual time.","title":"Testing"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/testing/#Snapshots","page":"Testing","text":"Render, then compare the plain text:\n\nusing Wicked.API\n\nbuffer = Buffer(1, 8)\nrender!(Frame(buffer), Label(\"Wicked\"), buffer.area)\n\n@assert occursin(\"Wicked\", plain_snapshot(buffer))\nassert_plain_snapshot(buffer, \"Wicked\")\n\nplain_snapshot strips styling and returns the on-screen text (rows joined by newlines), so assertions are easy to read and stable.","title":"Snapshots"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/testing/#Pilots","page":"Testing","text":"A pilot wraps a headless backend and drives your UI:\n\nPilot Drives\nRuntimePilot A managed runtime app.\nToolkitPilot A declarative Toolkit tree.\nWidgetPilot A single immediate-mode widget.\n\npilot = RuntimePilot(CounterApp(); height=3, width=24)\n\nsend!(pilot, :increment)                       # deliver a message\n@assert occursin(\"count = 1\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nToolkit pilots add input and query helpers:\n\npilot = ToolkitPilot(view(\"ready\"); height=5, width=32)\nfocus_element!(pilot, :deploy)\nkey!(pilot, :enter)\nbutton = query_one(pilot; id=:deploy, widget_type=Button, focused=true)","title":"Pilots"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/testing/#Virtual-time","page":"Testing","text":"Timers and subscriptions fire on a virtual clock, so tests never sleep and never flake:\n\nsend!(pilot, :tick)             # schedules a DelayCommand\nadvance_time!(pilot, 0.25)      # deterministically fires it\n@assert occursin(\"count = 2\", plain_snapshot(pilot))","title":"Virtual time"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/testing/#Semantics","page":"Testing","text":"Project an accessibility/testing tree and assert against roles and structure:\n\nsemantics = toolkit_semantic_tree(pilot.tree; label=\"Deployment\")\n@assert isempty(filter(d -> d.severity == :error, validate_semantics(semantics)))\n@assert occursin(\"deploy:ButtonRole\", semantic_snapshot(semantics))\n\nSee examples/testing_quickstart.jl.","title":"Semantics"},{"category":"section","location":"getting-started/#Getting-Started","page":"Getting Started","text":"","title":"Getting Started"},{"category":"section","location":"getting-started/#Install","page":"Getting Started","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/oleksandr-balyshyn/Wicked.jl\")\n\nThen bring in the single, stable developer facade:\n\nusing Wicked.API\n\nEverything documented in these guides is importable from Wicked.API. A small set of newer, still-internal helpers live on the Wicked module itself (see Cross-Library Features) and are reached with import Wicked.","title":"Install"},{"category":"section","location":"getting-started/#Core-concepts","page":"Getting Started","text":"A handful of types show up everywhere.\n\nType What it is\nBuffer A 2‑D grid of styled cells — the render target. Buffer(rows, cols).\nFrame A per-frame handle over a buffer, with an area.\nRect A rectangular region: Rect(row, column, height, width) (1-based).\nStyle / Color / Modifiers Foreground/background colors and text attributes.\nrender! Draws a widget into a buffer/frame within an area.\nhandle! Feeds an event (key/mouse) to a widget's state.\n\nRendering is explicit and headless-friendly: you can render any widget into a Buffer and inspect the result as text with plain_snapshot — no terminal required. That is what makes Wicked easy to test.\n\nusing Wicked.API\n\nbuffer = Buffer(3, 20)\nrender!(Frame(buffer), Paragraph(\"Hello, Wicked!\"), buffer.area)\n@assert occursin(\"Hello, Wicked!\", plain_snapshot(buffer))","title":"Core concepts"},{"category":"section","location":"getting-started/#Follow-a-tutorial","page":"Getting Started","text":"Hello, World — the smallest possible program.\nWeather App — a complete interactive TUI.","title":"Follow a tutorial"},{"category":"section","location":"getting-started/#Pick-a-layer","page":"Getting Started","text":"Immediate Mode — you drive the loop; each widget carries explicit state. Most control, least ceremony.\nManaged Runtime — an Elm-style model → update → view application with commands and subscriptions.\nDeclarative Toolkit — describe the UI with the @ui macro and components; the Toolkit reconciles it and manages state with hooks.","title":"Pick a layer"},{"category":"section","location":"getting-started/#Run-the-examples","page":"Getting Started","text":"Every file in the examples/ directory is a self-contained, runnable, CI-tested program:\n\njulia --project=. examples/immediate_quickstart.jl\njulia --project=. examples/toolkit_quickstart.jl\njulia --project=. examples/widget_gallery.jl\n\nThey are the fastest way to see real, working API for every feature.","title":"Run the examples"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Widget-Catalog","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Wicked ships 180+ widgets. All are importable from Wicked.API. Most render in immediate mode (render!) and many carry explicit state (*State) plus an event handler (handle!).","title":"Widget Catalog"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#By-category","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"","title":"By category"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Text-and-content","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Paragraph, Label, Heading, MarkupText, MarkdownView, SyntaxView, Pretty, RichLog, LogView, TextView, Static","title":"🧾 Text & content"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Collections","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"List, Table, DataTable, DataGrid, TreeTable, Tree, TreeView, OptionList, SelectionList, ListView","title":"📋 Collections"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Navigation","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Tabs, Menu, Breadcrumb, Pagination, Stepper, CommandPalette, Drawer, Carousel, Timeline","title":"🗂️ Navigation"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Controls","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Button, PushButton, Checkbox, Switch, Toggle, RadioGroup, RadioSet, Select, MultiSelect, ColorPicker, Calendar","title":"🎛️ Controls"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Input","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Input, TextArea, MaskedInput, PasswordField, NumberInput, SearchInput, CodeEditor","title":"⌨️ Input"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Visualization","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Gauge, LineGauge, Sparkline, BarChart, Chart, Histogram, Heatmap, Canvas, Plot, Digits","title":"📊 Visualization"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Feedback","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Notification, NotificationCenter, Alert, Badge, Spinner, Progress, ProgressGroup, Skeleton, LoadingIndicator, Status","title":"🔔 Feedback"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Structure","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Block, Panel, Card, Divider, Rule, Separator, Scrollbar, Collapsible, Popover, Overlay, Placeholder, Spacer, Padding, Clear","title":"🪟 Structure"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#App-chrome","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Header, Footer, TitleBar, KeyHint, HelpView, FileBrowser, TerminalView, ReplView, DevConsole, Inspector","title":"🗃️ App chrome"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Stateful-widget-pattern","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Stateful widgets follow a consistent contract: a widget value, a *State, a render!(buffer, widget, area, state) method, and a handle!(state, widget, event) method.\n\nusing Wicked.API\n\ntable = Table([\"Name\", \"Size\"], [[\"main.jl\", \"4 KB\"], [\"util.jl\", \"2 KB\"]])\nstate = TableState(selected_row=1)\n\nbuffer = Buffer(4, 30)\nrender!(buffer, table, buffer.area, state)\nhandle!(state, table, KeyEvent(Key(:down)); viewport_height=4)","title":"Stateful widget pattern"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#Cross-library-concept-map","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"Coming from another framework and want the right name? The api/widget_vocabulary.tsv ledger maps cross-library concepts (e.g. \"Bordered surface\", \"Panel/card\") to their Wicked widget names and state contracts.","title":"Cross-library concept map"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/widgets/#See-everything","page":"Widget Catalog","text":"examples/widget_gallery.jl renders a broad selection in one runnable program.","title":"See everything"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/weather-app/#Tutorial:-Weather-App","page":"Weather App","text":"A small but complete interactive TUI — a weather dashboard built on Wicked's managed runtime. It brings together a composite layout, several widgets, and the model → update → view loop. The forecast data is mocked (no network), so the whole thing is deterministic and runs headlessly.\n\nThe complete file is examples/weather_app.jl. Run it with:\n\njulia --project=. examples/weather_app.jl","title":"Tutorial: Weather App"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/weather-app/#What-it-looks-like","page":"Weather App","text":"                       Weather\n                      refresh #0\n╭─Cities─────────╮╭─Forecast─────────────────────────╮\n│› Kyiv          ││Kyiv — Clear                      │\n│  London        ││Temperature: 21°C                 │\n│  Tokyo         ││           Humidity 45%           │\n│  New York      ││Next 12 hours:                    │\n│                ││▁▂▃▅▆▇█▇▆▄▃▂                      │\n╰────────────────╯╰──────────────────────────────────╯\n ↑/↓  city   r  refresh   q  quit\n\nPress ↑/↓ to change city, r to refresh, q to quit.","title":"What it looks like"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/weather-app/#1.-Model","page":"Weather App","text":"The model is your application state — a plain mutable struct.\n\nmutable struct WeatherModel\n    selected::Int      # index into CITIES\n    refreshed::Int     # bumped on refresh\nend\n\nstruct WeatherApp <: WickedApp end\n\ninitialize(::WeatherApp) = WeatherModel(1, 0)","title":"1. Model"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/weather-app/#2.-View","page":"Weather App","text":"app_view is a pure function of the model returning a widget tree. Composite layouts are built with row/column and Element. Rendering the selection from the model (rather than from widget state) keeps the view pure.\n\nfunction city_list(selected::Int)\n    lines = [i == selected ? \"› $(city)\" : \"  $(city)\" for (i, city) in enumerate(CITIES)]\n    return Paragraph(join(lines, \"\\n\"))\nend\n\nfunction forecast_panel(city, f)\n    return column(\n        Element(Paragraph(\"$(city) — $(f.condition)\")),\n        Element(Paragraph(\"Temperature: $(f.temp_c)°C\")),\n        Element(Gauge(f.humidity / 100; label=\"Humidity $(f.humidity)%\")),\n        Element(Paragraph(\"Next 12 hours:\")),\n        Element(Sparkline(f.hourly));\n        constraints=[Length(1), Length(1), Length(1), Length(1), Length(1)],\n    )\nend\n\nfunction app_view(::WeatherApp, m::WeatherModel)\n    city = CITIES[m.selected]; forecast = FORECASTS[city]\n\n    body = row(\n        Element(Panel(city_list(m.selected); block=Block(title=\"Cities\"))),\n        Element(Panel(forecast_panel(city, forecast); block=Block(title=\"Forecast\")));\n        constraints=[Length(18), Fill(1)],\n    )\n\n    return column(\n        Element(TitleBar(\"Weather\"; subtitle=\"refresh #$(m.refreshed)\")),\n        Element(body),\n        Element(Footer([KeyHint(\"↑/↓\", \"city\"), KeyHint(\"r\", \"refresh\"), KeyHint(\"q\", \"quit\")]));\n        constraints=[Length(2), Fill(1), Length(1)],\n    )\nend\n\nNote how widgets compose: a Gauge for humidity, a Sparkline for the hourly temperatures, Panel/Block for framing, and a Footer of KeyHints.","title":"2. View"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/weather-app/#3.-Update","page":"Weather App","text":"update! mutates the model in response to a message and returns a command. Here it accepts both raw KeyEvents (a real terminal) and plain symbols (tests), so the same logic drives the app and its pilot.\n\nfunction update!(::WeatherApp, m::WeatherModel, message)\n    action = if message isa KeyEvent\n        code = message.key.code\n        code === :down ? :next :\n        code === :up ? :prev :\n        (code === :character && message.key.text == \"r\") ? :refresh :\n        (code === :character && message.key.text == \"q\") ? :quit : :ignore\n    else\n        message\n    end\n\n    if action === :next\n        m.selected = m.selected == length(CITIES) ? 1 : m.selected + 1\n        return FrameCommand()\n    elseif action === :prev\n        m.selected = m.selected == 1 ? length(CITIES) : m.selected - 1\n        return FrameCommand()\n    elseif action === :refresh\n        m.refreshed += 1\n        return FrameCommand()\n    elseif action === :quit\n        return ExitCommand(CITIES[m.selected])\n    end\n    return NoCommand()\nend","title":"3. Update"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/weather-app/#4.-Run-and-test-it","page":"Weather App","text":"A RuntimePilot runs the app headlessly, so the same program is its own test:\n\npilot = RuntimePilot(WeatherApp(); height=12, width=54)\n@assert occursin(\"Kyiv\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nsend!(pilot, :next)                       # or send!(pilot, KeyEvent(Key(:down)))\n@assert occursin(\"London\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nsend!(pilot, :refresh)\n@assert occursin(\"refresh #1\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nresult = send!(pilot, :quit)\n@assert result.exited\n\nIn a real terminal you would run the same WeatherApp on a live backend and feed it real key events — the model, view, and update logic do not change.","title":"4. Run and test it"},{"category":"section","location":"tutorials/weather-app/#Where-to-go-next","page":"Weather App","text":"Style the panels with roles and stylesheets — see Styling & Themes.\nAdd async refresh with a DelayCommand timer — see Managed Runtime.\nSwap the list for the stateful List widget with real selection state.","title":"Where to go next"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/immediate/#Immediate-Mode","page":"Immediate Mode","text":"Immediate mode is the most direct way to use Wicked: you own the frame loop, and each widget is drawn with explicit state you keep. It maps closely to Ratatui's model.","title":"Immediate Mode"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/immediate/#Draw-a-widget","page":"Immediate Mode","text":"using Wicked.API\n\nitems = List([\"Build\", \"Test\", \"Release\"])\nstate = ListState(selected=1)\n\nbuffer = Buffer(4, 24)\nrender!(Frame(buffer), items, buffer.area, state)\n\nrender! has two shapes:\n\nrender!(target, widget, area) — for stateless widgets.\nrender!(target, widget, area, state) — for stateful widgets, where state is a mutable value you own (e.g. ListState, TableState).\n\ntarget can be a Buffer or a Frame. area is a Rect.","title":"Draw a widget"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/immediate/#Handle-input","page":"Immediate Mode","text":"Feed events to a widget's state with handle!. It returns true when the event was consumed.\n\nhandle!(state, items, KeyEvent(Key(:down)); viewport_height=4)   # → selects \"Test\"\nhandle!(state, items, KeyEvent(Key(:up));   viewport_height=4)\n@assert state.selected == 1\n\nMouse events work too:\n\nevent = MouseEvent(Position(2, 3), LeftMouseButton, MouseRelease)\nhandle!(state, items, event, Rect(1, 1, 4, 24))","title":"Handle input"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/immediate/#Compose-a-screen","page":"Immediate Mode","text":"Split the buffer into regions with layout and render each widget into its own Rect:\n\nusing Wicked.API\n\nbuffer = Buffer(10, 48)\nframe  = Frame(buffer)\n\nrender!(frame, TitleBar(\"Dashboard\"; subtitle=\"immediate mode\"), Rect(1, 1, 2, 48))\n\nitems = List([\"Build\", \"Test\", \"Release\"]); items_state = ListState(selected=1)\nrender!(buffer, items, Rect(3, 1, 3, 18), items_state)\n\nrender!(buffer, Gauge(0.6; label=\"Build\"), Rect(7, 1, 1, 30))\nrender!(buffer, Status(\"Ready\"; severity=:success), Rect(8, 1, 3, 30))","title":"Compose a screen"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/immediate/#Selection-refinements","page":"Immediate Mode","text":"List and Table support Ratatui-style scrolling refinements:\n\n# Keep 1 row of context above/below the selection while scrolling\nList([\"a\", \"b\", \"c\", \"d\"]; scroll_padding=1)\n\n# Control the selection gutter: :always (default), :when_selected, or :never\nList([\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]; highlight_spacing=:when_selected)\n\nTable([\"Name\", \"Size\"], rows; scroll_padding=2)\n\nSee the full runnable version in examples/immediate_quickstart.jl.","title":"Selection refinements"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","text":"The complete developer surface is exported from Wicked.API — a single, stable facade. This page documents the headline symbols; the guides carry the narrative, and every feature has a runnable program under examples/.\n\nusing Wicked.API        # widgets, layout, runtime, toolkit, styling, testing\nimport Wicked           # newer cross-library helpers (see below)","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Rendering-core","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Rendering core"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Text-and-style","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Text & style"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Selection-widgets","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"Selection widgets"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Cross-library-helpers","page":"API Reference","text":"Scoped styling DSL, spring physics, adaptive color, keybinding help, canvas markers, and overlapping layout. Reach these with import Wicked (they are ready to promote into Wicked.API). See Cross-Library Features for usage.\n\nnote: The full surface\nWicked.API re-exports well over a thousand bindings — widgets, states, layout helpers, runtime and toolkit types, pilots, and semantic helpers. Browse them from the REPL with names(Wicked.API), or explore the categorized Widget Catalog.","title":"Cross-library helpers"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Core.Buffer","page":"API Reference","text":"A rectangular row-major terminal cell buffer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Core.Buffer"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Core.Frame","page":"API Reference","text":"The mutable render context for one terminal frame.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Core.Frame"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Core.Rect","page":"API Reference","text":"A one-based, half-open rectangular terminal region.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Core.Rect"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Core.Style","page":"API Reference","text":"A resolved terminal style.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Core.Style"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Core.Line","page":"API Reference","text":"A sequence of styled spans with horizontal alignment.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Core.Line"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Core.Text","page":"API Reference","text":"A sequence of styled terminal lines.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Core.Text"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.Styles.parse_color","page":"API Reference","text":"Parse default, named ANSI, indexed, hexadecimal, or RGB color syntax.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Styles.parse_color"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Widgets.List","page":"API Reference","text":"A scrollable list with explicit external selection state.\n\nscroll_padding keeps at least that many items visible before and after the selected item while scrolling (Ratatui scroll_padding parity). It is clamped so it never exceeds what the viewport can hold.\n\nhighlight_spacing controls the selection-symbol gutter (Ratatui HighlightSpacing parity):\n\n:always reserves the gutter on every row (default; preserves prior behavior).\n:when_selected reserves the gutter only while an item is selected.\n:never never reserves the gutter; selection is shown through highlight_style alone.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Widgets.List"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Widgets.ListState","page":"API Reference","text":"Externally owned selection and viewport state for List.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Widgets.ListState"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Widgets.Table","page":"API Reference","text":"A selectable table with constraint-sized columns and virtual viewport state.\n\nscroll_padding keeps at least that many rows visible before and after the selected row while scrolling (Ratatui scroll_padding parity), clamped so it never exceeds what the row viewport can hold.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Widgets.Table"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Widgets.Block","page":"API Reference","text":"A border, title, and padding surface.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Widgets.Block"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.styled_text","page":"API Reference","text":"styled_text(block) -> Text\n\nBuild a Wicked Text using nested scoped-style combinators. block receives a StyledTextBuilder; use styled, emit!, and newline! inside it. Trailing spans are flushed into a final line.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.styled_text"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.StyledTextBuilder","page":"API Reference","text":"Mutable accumulator used while building a Text with scoped style combinators.\n\nHolds the finished lines, the spans of the line currently being built, and a stack of styles. The top of the stack is the style applied to newly emitted text; styled pushes a merged style and pops it when its block returns.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.StyledTextBuilder"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.styled","page":"API Reference","text":"styled(block, builder; fg, bg, bold, dim, italic, underline, reverse, ...)\n\nApply a merged style to everything block emits into builder, then restore the previous style. Scopes nest: an inner styled merges its options onto the enclosing style, so styled(b; bold=true) do; styled(b; fg=:green) do ... end produces bold-green text. Returns builder for chaining.\n\ntext = styled_text() do b\n    styled(b; fg=:cyan, bold=true) do\n        emit!(b, \"Deploy \")\n        styled(b; fg=:green) do\n            emit!(b, \"ready\")\n        end\n    end\n    newline!(b)\n    styled(b; dim=true) do\n        emit!(b, \"press q to quit\")\n    end\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.styled"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.emit!","page":"API Reference","text":"emit!(builder, content; kwargs...)\n\nEmit inline text into builder. With no keywords the text uses the current scoped style; with keywords (fg, bold, …) it is wrapped in a one-shot styled scope so emit!(builder, \"text\"; fg=:red) styles just that fragment.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.emit!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.newline!","page":"API Reference","text":"Finish the current line in builder and begin a new one.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.newline!"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.Spring","page":"API Reference","text":"A damped-spring configuration.\n\nConstruct with a time step and, optionally, an angular_frequency (stiffness, in radians/second) and damping_ratio. Advance a value toward a target with spring_update.\n\nspring = Spring(1 / 60; angular_frequency = 8.0, damping_ratio = 0.6)\nposition, velocity = 0.0, 0.0\nfor _ in 1:120\n    position, velocity = spring_update(spring, position, velocity, 1.0)\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.Spring"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.spring_update","page":"API Reference","text":"spring_update(spring, position, velocity, target) -> (position, velocity)\n\nAdvance position/velocity one time step toward target under spring. Returns the new (position, velocity). Feed the results back in on the next frame; the value converges to target with velocity approaching zero.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.spring_update"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.adaptive_color","page":"API Reference","text":"adaptive_color(light, dark; dark_background=true) -> Color\n\nReturn dark when rendering on a dark terminal background and light otherwise, mirroring Lip Gloss AdaptiveColor. light/dark may be Color values or any value accepted by parse_color (a named/hex/rgb string).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.adaptive_color"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.downsample_color","page":"API Reference","text":"downsample_color(color, level) -> Color\n\nReduce color to the terminal color level, returning a Color that renders the same as letting the backend degrade the original. level is one of :truecolor (unchanged), :ansi256, :ansi16, or :none (the default color).\n\nNamed/16-color and indexed colors are preserved where the level allows and folded into the 16-color range for :ansi16; RGB colors are quantised with the same math the ANSI backend uses.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.downsample_color"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.KeyBinding","page":"API Reference","text":"A keybinding: a key label, its description, and whether it is active.\n\nThe single source of truth for help rendering. Build a Vector{KeyBinding} once and derive both the footer hints and the short help line from it, so keys and their documentation never drift apart.\n\nbindings = [\n    KeyBinding(\"q\", \"quit\"),\n    KeyBinding(\"s\", \"save\"; enabled = document_dirty),\n]\nFooter(help_hints(bindings))\nshort_help(bindings; max_width = width)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.KeyBinding"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.help_hints","page":"API Reference","text":"Return KeyHints for the enabled bindings (for Footer / HelpView).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.help_hints"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.short_help","page":"API Reference","text":"short_help(bindings; separator=\" • \", max_width=nothing, overflow=\"…\") -> String\n\nRender the enabled bindings as a single-line help string. Each entry is \"<key> <description>\", joined by separator. When max_width is given, entries are included greedily until the line (plus an overflow marker if any remain) would exceed max_width columns; the marker is then appended.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.short_help"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#Wicked.PixelCanvas","page":"API Reference","text":"A sub-cell pixel grid rendered with a chosen glyph marker.\n\nrows/cols are in terminal cells; the pixel grid is rows*pixel_height by cols*pixel_width. Set pixels with pixel_set! (1-based x horizontal, y vertical) and render with pixel_render.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.PixelCanvas"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.pixel_set!","page":"API Reference","text":"pixel_set!(canvas, x, y, on=true) -> Bool\n\nSet the pixel at 1-based column x and row y. Returns false (a no-op) when the coordinate is outside the grid, so callers can plot without bounds-checking.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.pixel_set!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.pixel_render","page":"API Reference","text":"pixel_render(canvas) -> Vector{String}\n\nRender the pixel grid to one string per terminal-cell row, mapping each cell's sub-pixels to the canvas's marker glyph.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.pixel_render"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#Wicked.overlap_layout","page":"API Reference","text":"overlap_layout(area, lengths; direction=:horizontal, overlap=1) -> Vector{Rect}\n\nLay out segments of the given lengths along direction inside area, with each segment starting overlap cells before the previous one ends, so adjacent segments share overlap cells (use overlap=1 for shared single-cell borders, overlap=0 for ordinary abutting segments). Each returned Rect is clipped to area; lengths that run past the edge are truncated.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Wicked.overlap_layout"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/layout/#Layout","page":"Layout","text":"Wicked's layout engine is Ratatui-inspired: constraints describe how space is divided along an axis, flex alignment distributes leftover space, and grids handle two dimensions.","title":"Layout"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/layout/#Constraints","page":"Layout","text":"Split an axis with a vector of constraints:\n\nConstraint Meaning\nLength(n) Exactly n cells.\nMin(n) At least n cells.\nMax(n) At most n cells.\nPercentage(p) p% of the available space.\nRatio(a, b) a/b of the available space.\nFill(weight) A weighted share of the remainder.\n\nusing Wicked.API\n\nrow(\n    Element(Label(\"sidebar\")),\n    Element(Label(\"content\")),\n    Element(Label(\"aside\"));\n    constraints=[Length(20), Fill(1), Percentage(25)],\n)","title":"Constraints"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/layout/#Rows,-columns,-stacks,-grids","page":"Layout","text":"# Horizontal / vertical containers\nrow(children...; constraints, gap, alignment, margin)\ncolumn(children...; constraints, gap, alignment, margin)\n\n# Overlay stack (later children layer above earlier ones)\nstack(children...)\n\n# Two-axis grid\ngrid(Element(Label(\"a\")), Element(Label(\"b\")); rows=[Length(1)], columns=[Fill(1), Fill(1)])\n\n# Center a fixed-size child\ncentered(Element(Label(\"modal\")); height=3, width=20)","title":"Rows, columns, stacks, grids"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/layout/#Flex-alignment","page":"Layout","text":"row/column distribute leftover space with a FlexAlignment:\n\nStartFlex, CenterFlex, EndFlex, SpaceBetween, SpaceAround, SpaceEvenly — matching CSS flexbox and Ratatui's Flex.\n\ncolumn(Element(Label(\"top\")), Element(Label(\"bottom\")); alignment=SpaceBetween, gap=1)","title":"Flex alignment"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/layout/#Migration-aliases","page":"Layout","text":"Porting from another framework? Directional aliases read naturally:\n\nhstack / vstack, hbox / vbox, horizontal / vertical\nhsplit / vsplit\nzstack / overlay\nUpper-case HStack / VStack / HBox / VBox / ZStack\n\nThey all resolve to row / column / stack.","title":"Migration aliases"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/layout/#Shared-borders","page":"Layout","text":"For blocks that should share a border column or row, use the additive overlap_layout helper (see Cross-Library Features):\n\nimport Wicked\nWicked.overlap_layout(Rect(1, 1, 3, 20), [10, 10]; overlap=1)   # segments share 1 column\n\nSee examples/layout_quickstart.jl.","title":"Shared borders"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/toolkit/#Declarative-Toolkit","page":"Declarative Toolkit","text":"The Toolkit is Wicked's declarative layer. You describe the UI as an element tree; the Toolkit reconciles it against retained state using stable key/id values, routes events, manages focus, and runs component effects. It feels like Textual, React, and Jetpack Compose — while still rendering through Wicked's immediate-mode core.","title":"Declarative Toolkit"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/toolkit/#The-@ui-macro","page":"Declarative Toolkit","text":"The @ui macro turns zero-argument do blocks into element children, so a UI tree reads top-to-bottom:\n\nusing Wicked.API\n\nconst PRIMARY = then(\n    element_modifier(focusable=true),\n    element_modifier(classes=[:primary], style_role=:primary),\n)\n\nview(status) = @ui column(; constraints=[Length(1), Length(3)], gap=0) do\n    Element(Label(\"Deployment: $status\"); id=:status, key=:status)\n    element(Button(\"Deploy\", :deploy); id=:deploy, key=:deploy, modifier=PRIMARY)\nend\n\nElement(widget; id, key, ...) wraps any widget as a tree node.\nelement(widget; ...) is the same, with light-weight defaults.\nkey keeps local state stable across rebuilds; id addresses a node for focus, queries, and semantics.","title":"The @ui macro"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/toolkit/#Reusable-modifiers","page":"Declarative Toolkit","text":"element_modifier(...) bundles element properties — classes, style_role, style_patch, focusable, disabled, hidden, tab_index, key/id — into a preset applied with modify or the modifier= keyword. Chain presets with then(...). These read like Compose modifiers or Tailwind class sets while staying fully typed.\n\nconst FOCUSABLE = element_modifier(focusable=true)\nconst DANGER    = then(FOCUSABLE, element_modifier(classes=[:danger], style_role=:error))","title":"Reusable modifiers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/toolkit/#Drive-it-with-a-pilot","page":"Declarative Toolkit","text":"pilot = ToolkitPilot(view(\"ready\"); height=5, width=32)\n@assert occursin(\"Deployment: ready\", plain_snapshot(pilot))\n\nfocus_element!(pilot, :deploy)\nkey!(pilot, :enter)                       # emits the :deploy message\n@assert :deploy in pilot.messages\n\nquery_one(pilot; id=:deploy, widget_type=Button, focused=true)   # semantic query","title":"Drive it with a pilot"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/toolkit/#Components-and-hooks","page":"Declarative Toolkit","text":"Components own local state managed by hooks — a React/Compose-style API. The framework retains a ComponentState for each stable key, so remembered values and running effects survive re-renders.\n\ncounter = component(initial=0, key=:counter, id=:counter) do state\n    n = component_value(state)\n    use_effect!(state, :n, (n,)) do _\n        # runs on mount and whenever n changes; return a cleanup closure\n        () -> nothing\n    end\n    \"Local count: $n\"\nend\n\nAvailable hooks include:\n\nremember! — retain a value across renders.\nstate_binding — a get/set binding into retained state.\nuse_effect! — run a side effect with a cleanup, keyed on dependencies.\nuse_resource! / load_async_resource! — load async data.\nlaunched_effect! / side_effect! — fire-and-forget effects.","title":"Components and hooks"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/toolkit/#Screens","page":"Declarative Toolkit","text":"Toolkit apps can keep a stack of screens (ScreenStack) and navigate with commands like PushScreen, PopScreen, and ReplaceWithScreen — mirroring Textual's screen model — for modal dialogs, wizards, and routed navigation.\n\nThe full runnable version — including semantics, context, and component lifecycle — is in examples/toolkit_quickstart.jl.","title":"Screens"},{"category":"section","location":"","page":"Home","text":"<p align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"assets/logo.svg\" width=\"150\" alt=\"Wicked.jl logo\">\n</p>","title":"Home"},{"category":"section","location":"#Wicked.jl","page":"Home","text":"Serious terminal user interfaces, in pure Julia.\n\nWicked.jl gives you the rendering power of Ratatui, the composition model of Textual & Jetpack Compose, and the ergonomics of Terminus & Bubble Tea — as one Julia-first framework with no non-Julia dependencies.\n\nwarning: Pre-release\nWicked.jl is 0.0.1 and under active development. The implementation and automated test coverage are extensive, but broad real-terminal validation and a release-candidate freeze are still ahead. Pin the commit for anything you ship.","title":"Wicked.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#Three-cooperating-layers","page":"Home","text":"Most terminal libraries make you pick a philosophy. Wicked gives you three layers over one fast, Unicode-correct rendering core — use the one that fits, and mix them freely.\n\nLayer Use it when Feels like\nImmediate mode You own the frame loop and want direct control Ratatui\nManaged runtime You want one observable app lifecycle Bubble Tea / Elm\nDeclarative Toolkit You want components, hooks, and reconciliation Textual / React / Compose","title":"Three cooperating layers"},{"category":"section","location":"#A-first-taste","page":"Home","text":"using Wicked.API\n\nbuffer = Buffer(5, 42)                 # 5 rows × 42 cols\nframe  = Frame(buffer)\nrender!(frame, Paragraph(\"Deploy safely. Observe everything.\"), frame.area)\n\nprint(plain_snapshot(buffer))          # render anywhere — even headless","title":"A first taste"},{"category":"section","location":"#What's-inside","page":"Home","text":"⚡ Rendering core — cell buffers, frames, minimal diffs, Unicode/East-Asian width, and clipping.\n🧱 Layout — Ratatui-style constraints (Length, Min, Max, Percentage, Ratio, Fill), flexbox distribution, grids, docking, and flow.\n🧰 180+ widgets — lists, tables, trees, tabs, gauges, charts, canvases, inputs, forms, command palettes, notifications, and more.\n🎨 Styling & themes — a typed style core plus CSS-like stylesheets with selectors, pseudo-states, roles, and light/dark/high-contrast.\n🧭 Runtime — model/update/view with commands, subscriptions, timers, and cancellation.\n🧩 Toolkit — keyed reconciliation, a @ui macro, React/Compose-style hooks, focus, routed events, and screens.\n🌈 Rich output — Kitty/Sixel graphics, braille & block canvases, markdown, and syntax highlighting.\n🧪 Testing — headless buffers, snapshots, semantic assertions, pilots, and virtual time.","title":"What's inside"},{"category":"section","location":"#Install","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/oleksandr-balyshyn/Wicked.jl\")\n\nContinue to Getting Started.","title":"Install"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/styling/#Styling-and-Themes","page":"Styling & Themes","text":"Wicked has a typed styling core plus a CSS-like stylesheet system, roles, and themes — so you can style a single span or theme an entire application.","title":"Styling & Themes"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/styling/#The-style-core","page":"Styling & Themes","text":"using Wicked.API\n\nStyle(foreground=AnsiColor(6), background=DefaultColor(), modifiers=BOLD | UNDERLINE)\n\nColors: AnsiColor(0..15) (named 16), IndexedColor(0..255) (256-color), RGBColor(r, g, b) (truecolor), DefaultColor().\nModifiers: BOLD, DIM, ITALIC, UNDERLINE, DOUBLE_UNDERLINE, BLINK, REVERSED, HIDDEN, STRIKETHROUGH — combine with |.\nStylePatch: a partial update that preserves unspecified properties (StylePatch(add_modifiers=UNDERLINE)).\n\nColor strings are parsed by parse_color: names (\"bright-cyan\"), hex (\"#00d7ff\"), \"rgb(0, 215, 255)\", or \"indexed(45)\".","title":"The style core"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/styling/#CSS-like-stylesheets","page":"Styling & Themes","text":"Parse a stylesheet with selectors and pseudo-states:\n\nsheet = parse_stylesheet(\"\"\"\nButton.primary        { color: bright-cyan; }\nButton.primary:focus  { modifiers: bold underline; }\nButton.secondary      { color: yellow; }\n\"\"\")\n\nSelectors support widget types, .class, and pseudo-states like :focus, mirroring Textual's TCSS.","title":"CSS-like stylesheets"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/styling/#Themes-and-roles","page":"Styling & Themes","text":"A Theme maps semantic roles to styles, so widgets style by intent (:accent, :error, :text) rather than hard-coded colors:\n\ntheme = Theme(:app; roles=Dict(\n    :text   => Style(foreground=AnsiColor(15)),\n    :accent => Style(foreground=AnsiColor(6), modifiers=BOLD),\n))\n\nCombine a theme and stylesheets into a StyleEngine, then hand it to a Toolkit tree or pilot:\n\nengine = StyleEngine(; theme, stylesheets=[sheet])\n\nroot = column(\n    Element(Label(\"Deployments\"); id=:title, key=:title, style_role=:accent),\n    Element(Button(\"Deploy\", :deploy); id=:deploy, key=:deploy, classes=[:primary], focusable=true);\n    constraints=[Length(1), Length(3)],\n)\n\npilot = ToolkitPilot(root; height=4, width=28, styles=engine)\n\nThemes support light, dark, and high-contrast preferences, and terminal palette downgrade when truecolor is unavailable.","title":"Themes and roles"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/styling/#Adaptive-color-and-downsampling","page":"Styling & Themes","text":"For per-value light/dark pairs and profile downsampling (Lip Gloss style), see Cross-Library Features:\n\nimport Wicked\nWicked.adaptive_color(\"black\", \"white\"; dark_background=true)   # → white on dark bg\nWicked.downsample_color(RGBColor(255, 128, 0), :ansi256)        # truecolor → 256\n\nSee examples/styling_quickstart.jl.","title":"Adaptive color & downsampling"}]
}
